                <head>394. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The White House Staff Notes for November 6 include the following item concerning
                    developments in relations with Egypt: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">“Egypt’s Envoy Talks to <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1"
                                    >Nasser</persName>.</hi>—Egypt’s Ambassador to the US says he
                            recently told <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName> that we
                            are not ‘out to get’ Egypt or <persName corresp="#p_NNNGA1"
                                >Nasser</persName>, but that we are forced to counter any <persName
                                corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName> moves which assist the <gloss
                                target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>. He said he urged on <persName
                                corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName> a three-stage program of: (1)
                            a propaganda ‘truce’ with the US, (2) a quick settlement with Canal
                            Company shareholders, to make possible the unblocking of dollars, and
                            (3) ‘deemphasis’ on Egyptian contacts with the Soviet bloc. <persName
                                corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName> reportedly responded only to
                            ask whether we would accept trainees in various fields, including the
                            military. His Ambassador could not answer, <pb facs="0822" n="790"
                                xml:id="pg_790"/> but suggested he try West Germany instead.”
                            (Eisenhower Library, Whitman File, <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                                >Eisenhower</persName> Diaries; <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                                >Eisenhower</persName> initialed the notes.)</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The Embassy in Cairo conveyed reports received from Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_HA1">Hussein</persName> to the Department of State in telegram
                    1099 from Cairo, October 30, and in telegram 1125 from Cairo, November 3.
                    (Department of State, Central Files, 611.74/10–3057 and 611.74/11–357,
                    respectively)</p>
            </div>
